{"article_id":"cOxK1CUSIongNP2D","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Still fewer than five days old ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"the House Republican bill","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to repeal Obamacare","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"has an uncertain legislative path ahead .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"And no small part of the blame goes to President Donald Trump .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Competing interests among Republicans threaten to derail the party 's urgent mission","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"of gutting the Affordable Care Act .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"After publicly endorsing the bill","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"developed by House Speaker Paul Ryan and other GOP leaders ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Trump and some of his top officials held a flurry of closed-door meetings this week with critics of the legislation","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to try to move lawmakers toward a consensus .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"But in these private gatherings , Trump appears to be sending some conflicting messages .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"After sessions with leaders of influential conservative groups and lawmakers , administration officials signaled","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that the President was open to scrapping Obamacare 's Medicaid expansion sooner than 2020","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"-- - the date","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"that is stated in the House GOP bill -","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"a change","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"that could scare away moderate Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"The confusion over the Medicaid portion of the Obamacare bill appears to be another example of Trump 's eagerness","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to strike deals","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and negotiate","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"-- and how that tendency can sometimes complicate things for members of his own party .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"House conservatives openly acknowledge","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"that they are seizing on Trump 's reputation as a dealmaker","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"to try to reshape the health care overhaul .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"`` I like that about this president .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"He understands","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"that no product is the final product , ''","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Idaho Republican Rep. Raul Labrador said Friday .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Just the development","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that the White House is publicly entertaining the change","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"sent House GOP leaders scrambling to answer questions","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"about whether the White House and congressional leaders see eye-to-eye on a major component of the health care bill .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"`` I think","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"right now","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that would be very difficult to do , ''","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"House Majority Leader Kevin McCarthy told reporters in a news conference Friday morning","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"when asked","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"if he supported moving up the sunset of Medicaid expansion .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Later in the day , White House press secretary Sean Spicer sided with House GOP leaders ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"saying :","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"`` Right now , the date","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"that 's in the bill","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"is what the President supports . ''","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Next week could bring more tumult","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"-- the Congressional Budget office is expected to release its score of the House health care bill ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"which could show","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"that millions will lose their coverage .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"The anticipated bad news is poised to be one more area","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"where Trump could veer from the party message .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"The Medicaid section in the House Republicans ' Obamacare repeal bill was carefully crafted ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"and congressional leaders warn","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"that disrupting it now could imperil the bill .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"Scrapping the expansion earlier could help win over a handful of conservative votes ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"but it could cost GOP votes in the Senate","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"where nearly 20 lawmakers hail from expansion states .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"`` The needle","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that leadership is trying to thread right now","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"is exactly that between people","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"who want to take things out of the bill","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"and make it less","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"than it is","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"and those of us","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"who are already struggling with the effectiveness on the most vulnerable , ''","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"said Rep. Tom MacArthur , a New Jersey Republican","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"who is a co-chair of the House 's moderate Tuesday Group .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"How to tackle the federal Medicaid expansion has emerged as one of the toughest obstacles for Republican leaders .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Some 31 states","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"-- including 16 with Republican governors --","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"took advantage of the program","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"and found it to be a successful tool","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"to insure low-income adults at little cost to their states .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"The politics of Medicaid expansion has scrambled traditional political fault lines .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"It 's not just a simple break between moderates and conservatives","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"-- the differences of opinion are also between expansion and non-expansion state lawmakers .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Those from expansion states have worked closely with leadership","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"to try to protect their federal match dollars for as long","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"as possible","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"while those from non-expansion states have argued","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"the Medicaid expansion should sunset as soon as possible .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"In recent days , senior administration officials have wooed conservative lawmakers in private meetings and even at a bowling party at the White House","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"-- all as the administration has continued to publicly back the bill","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"crafted by Ryan and committee chairs .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"But GOP leadership aides caution","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"while they could still make some changes","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"in order to get additional support before the final House vote ,","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"they do n't anticipate the kinds of wholesale changes","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"that House Freedom Caucus members are demanding .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"If Trump has veered off-message ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Republican leaders have managed to maintain iron-fisted control over their bill ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"successfully passing it out of both the Energy and Commerce and the Ways and Means committees","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"without a single substantive amendment","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"-- despite sessions of a combined 45 hours .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Rep. Joe Barton , a Republican from Texas , filed an amendment in the Energy and Commerce Committee markup","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"that would have sunset the Medicaid expansion sooner than the 2020 deadline in the bill ,","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"but he pulled the proposal","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"before it came up for a vote .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Energy and Commerce Chairman Greg Walden told Trump behind closed doors Friday","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"that the Medicaid language in the House health care bill is here to stay ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"according to a source familiar with the meeting .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Walden made clear","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"that the provision","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"that would sunset Obamacare 's Medicaid expansion in 2020","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"was drafted in consultation with key players ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"including wary red-state governors , lawmakers and the White House itself .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Walden 's comments came","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"as sources told CNN","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"the White House , after two days of meetings with conservative lawmakers and outside groups , is amenable to cutting that transition window down to 2017 .","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"A separate source noted","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"that the White House was in agreement on the language during the final stages","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"of drafting the bill this weekend .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"As it stands ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"there are no changes","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"planned in the House bill in the weeks ahead ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"the source said .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Instead , the Senate will be the forum for any substantive shifts .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"`` I ca n't speak for the Senate ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"but we 're comfortable with our product","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"as is , ''","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"the source said .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"Conservatives","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"opposed to the bill","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"are ignoring warnings from GOP leaders","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"that the bill will not get a significant face-lift ,","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"insisting","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"they have leverage","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"because the measure ca n't pass","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"without buy-in from a major chunk of the Freedom Caucus .","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"They are also eyeing the House Rules Committee ,","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"which is the final stop","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"before the measure gets to the floor ,","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"as the opportunity","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"to insert significant modifications .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"`` We 're going to negotiate with the White House and with our leadership","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"and they need our votes , ''","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Labrador said .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"House Freedom Caucus Chairman Mark Meadows told reporters Friday","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"that after the White House 's meeting , he feels confident","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"that the administration is willing to play ball .","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"`` I am very confident","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"based on my conversations with the White House","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"that there is a willingness","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"to negotiate in good faith things","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"that drive down health care premiums , ''","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"the North Carolina Republican said .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"`` That being said ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"do I expect","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"all of the issues","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"that many of the Freedom Caucus members would like to have","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"will be in a final bill","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"that passes ?","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"The answer is no .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"So , it 's about a good faith negotiation . '' No matter what , expect the talks and proposals to continue .","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"`` Despite what you hear in the press ,","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"healthcare is coming along great .","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"We are talking to many groups","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"and it will end in a beautiful picture ! ''","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"Trump tweeted Thursday .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":319,"left":0,"right":318,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":318,"left":203,"right":317,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":166,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":164,"right":165,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":163,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":1,"right":162,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":161,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":161,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":187,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":176,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":169,"right":175,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":169,"left":167,"right":168,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":167,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":12,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":13,"right":173,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":173,"left":171,"right":172,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":14,"right":170,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":179,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent"